node.text:
We couldn’t be more proud of our 34 dancers and faculty, coaches, choreographers, and parents! THANK YOU @yagp for all you are doing to ensure the future of dance! NOTE: The list below is in addition to our previous awards of the ‘21 Season! Please help us in congratulating:

1st PLACE :
“La Donna” and “Wicked Games” (Ensembles)
.
2nd PLACE: Megan McAdoo (Senior Contemporary)
.
2nd PLACE: Annie Laws 
(Pre-Competitive Classical)
.
3rd PLACE: Annie Laws (Pre-Competitive Contemporary)
.
TOP 12 SOLOISTS:
.
Eliza Soto (Senior Classical and Senior Contemporary)
.
Julianna McKelvey (Junior Contemporary)
.
Julianne Bjerke (Junior Contemporary)
.
Zoey Reese (Pre-Competitive Classical)
.

TOP 24 CLASSICAL JUNIORS:
Abigail Weber
Gavin Teague
Julianna McKelvey
Julianne Bjerke
Leah Carter

TOP 12 ENSEMBLES:
.
 “Ocean and Pearls” Julianna McKelvey and Leah Carter 
(Ensembles)
.
“The Distance” Madeleine Chen and Eliza Soto (Ensembles) 
.
“Penny Lane” (Ensembles) 

INVITED TO INTERNATIONAL FINALS:

Abigail Weber 
Annie Laws
Julianna McKelvey
Julianne Bjerke
Tobias Weber
Zoey Reese
“La Donna”
“Wicked Games”
“The Distance”
“Ocean and Pearls”
“Penny Lane”
“Harlequinade Pas De Deux”
“Phases”

Keep watching our feed for updates and scroll back through recent posts to learn more about our 6th consecutive “Outstanding School” award and much more! 
.
#thedallasconservatory 
#yagpdallas #yagp2021 #yagpdallas2021

CONGRATULATIONS @meganmcadoo on your $100,000 scholarship to PACE UNIVERSITY!!! 😱🎉⬇️
.
Congratulations to Megan McAdoo, age 18! This busy dancer, choreographer and actress/singer was just awarded a dream scholarship to Pace through the NYCDA Foundation Scholarship Program. After an amazing season competing with a self-choreographed solo, Megan was recently invited all the way through to final callbacks in NYC (also through NYCDA) for the new National Tour of “CATS”! She is completing her last year of high school at The Dallas Conservatory / TDC Academics where she has performed in Nutcracker and musical theater works, worked with many leading choreographers and guests, and is now choreographing on her peers. 🔥🔥🔥We extend our deepest gratitude to @nycda and @lanterijoe for NYCDA’s life-changing  College Scholarship program! Pace @pacecommercialdance is a DREAM COME TRUE and we are all thrilled! 🎉🤩🤸‍♀️
.
#thedallasconservatory #nycda #paceuniversity

#flashbackfriday June SI with @kathryn_morgan ❤️🩰 Looking forward to July and August sessions! SEE IMPORTANT UPDATES ⬇️⬇️⬇️
.
Have you been wondering if you can still fit in more amazing dance training this summer? YOU CAN - flights are inexpensive and lots of  housing is still available near our gorgeous studios for ages 8-22. Change your life and study for a week or longer at TDC where international, world-class training and networking is what we offer every day, 300+ days of the year! Choose 1-4 weeks for late summer (July 19-Aug 13) or audition for year-round. DM us or follow link in bio! More details⬇️
.
TDC At-A-Glance:

🌟 6-time winner of the @yagp Outstanding School Award 2016-21 
🌟 Over 100 top awards at YAGP, @nycda , @tremainedance and more since 2008.
🌟International year-round and summer faculty with credits from the Bolshoi to Broadway! 
🌟We train Pre-Pro ballet and commercial dancers as well as Broadway triple threats  8-17 // Professional Classical Division Ages 15-22 (one spot has become available -auditioning immediately) - and as always, we teach recreational dancers of all ages 18 months-Adult in all styles!!
🌟Auditions happening now for all divisions and companies (no audition requirements for recreational classes) 
🌟😱🤩CHANGE YOUR LIFE! Follow the link in bio or DM us today. We will get right back to you and arrange a phone conversation free of charge if you’d like! We look forward to meeting you!!😘🎉👯‍♀️
.
